# Low-Latency Desktop Gaming Agent

## Goal

Build a desktop AI agent that can play games in real time.

Gaming is the first proof point because it makes latency obvious. If the agent can understand the screen, make decisions, and control the game quickly, the same architecture can later operate normal desktop software.

## Core Positioning

> A real-time desktop agent that sees your screen and controls your computer with low latency.

Gaming is the demo.
Desktop automation is the larger platform.

---

# Product Principles

## 1. Latency First

The agent must feel instant.

Target loop:

- Screen capture: 5–15ms
- Perception: 10–50ms
- Action decision: 1–20ms
- Input execution: 1–5ms
- Total reflex loop: under 100ms

Do not call a large LLM every frame.

---

## 2. Hybrid Intelligence

Use two brains:

### Fast Controller

Runs many times per second.

Handles:
- movement
- aiming/clicking
- dodging
- combat reactions
- menu navigation
- repeated game loops

This should be local and small.

### Slow Planner

Runs occasionally.

Handles:
- strategy
- goals
- “what should I do next?”
- quests
- resource planning
- inventory choices
- recovery from confusion

This can use a larger VLM/LLM.

---

# High-Level Architecture

```text
Game Screen
